---
// src/pages/_site-updates/2026-06-28-international-marketing-copy.astro
export const updateMeta = {
  date: '2026-06-28',
  title: 'ADR-0037 Slice 3: international marketing copy',
  tags: ['pricing', 'footer', 'international', 'adr-0037'],
};
---
<article class="border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] pl-6">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">June 28, 2026</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">
    Shipped ADR-0037 Slice 3 (international parity, marketing copy). Two
    user-visible copy additions on <code>breederhq-www</code> close the
    last remaining slice of the International Parity Sprint, paired with
    Slices 1A.3 + 1D + 2A + 2B that shipped in the <code>breederhq</code>
    monorepo over the preceding sprint window.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-1">Footer</h3>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3">
    Added under the brand-column tagline:
    "Serving breeders in the US, UK, Canada, Australia, and Europe."
    Site-wide footprint statement; appears on every page that mounts
    <code>Footer.astro</code> (i.e. every public marketing page).
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-1">Pricing page</h3>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3">
    Added under each plan's price block on <a href="/pricing" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/pricing</a>:
    "Billed in USD. International cards accepted." Renders in both the
    founders-promo branch (Pro + Enterprise with FOUNDER50) and the
    standard branch (Standard plan). Schema.org structured data already
    declared <code>priceCurrency: "USD"</code>; this surfaces the same
    fact in the user-visible UI alongside the new international
    statement of fact.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-1">ContactForm (no-op disposition)</h3>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3">
    ADR-0037 §176 named <code>ContactForm.astro</code> as a target to
    "ensure the international + prefix copy is accurate." Pre-flight
    confirmed it already is: the hint at line 124 reads "We default to
    US format. Start with + and your country code for international
    (e.g. +44, +91)." The error copy at line 126 explains the
    international convention symmetrically. US default behavior
    (<code>DEFAULT_COUNTRY: CountryCode = 'US'</code>) is preserved per
    the ADR + the standing "don't gratuitously change defaults" memory.
    No edits to <code>ContactForm.astro</code> in this slice.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-1">Slice 3 scope discipline</h3>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3">
    Per ADR-0037, no language-switcher / multilingual-UI claims were
    added. No schema, API, or backend coupling. No help-article or FAQ
    surfaces touched (hidden-sibling audit found no contradictory
    US-only or international-footprint claims that would have made the
    narrow scope dishonest). Single coherent commit on
    <code>master</code> per the cross-repo / master-branch rule.
  </p>
</article>
